Package: intraitR
Title: Morphological Trait Analysis Toolkit for Freshwater Fish
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Aurele", "Toussaint", , "aurele.toussaint@cnrs.fr", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A toolkit for the analysis of morphological traits in freshwater
    fish, from raw two-dimensional landmark digitization to derived
    morphological ratios, morphological space, and functional trait space.
    Building on the geometric morphometric framework implemented in
    'geomorph' (Adams, Collyer and Kaliontzopoulou, 2024), the package
    provides convenience functions to import landmark data from 'tpsDig'
    files or generic spreadsheets, perform Generalised Procrustes Analysis,
    compute classical linear morphometric ratios used in fish ecomorphology,
    build and visualise morphological and functional trait spaces, quantify
    intraspecific morphological variability, and estimate measurement error
    from replicated digitization, following Bailey and Byrnes (1990)
    <doi:10.2307/2992207> and Fruciano (2016) <doi:10.1007/s00427-016-0537-4>.
    The package also implements the specific 11-measurement, 9-ratio
    digitization and trait protocol of the FISHMORPH database (Brosse et al.,
    2021) <doi:10.1111/geb.13395>. Alongside simulated example data sets, a
    real landmark data set from an electrofishing survey of eight freshwater
    fish species (T-26, La Saudrune, Adour-Garonne basin, France) is
    included, with a complete worked pipeline demonstrating the full
    workflow on field data.
